	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imprisoned the Consuls for refusing to allow certain exemptions from the levy but remitted a fine at popular entreaty (Cic. Leg. 3.20; Liv. Oxy. Per. 55). Curiatius also urged the Consuls to relieve grain prices (Val. Max. 3.7.3; cf. Liv. Per. 55)." .
